# anima — environment template
# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored (.gitignore: .env, .env.*).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH POLICY — READ THIS (operational incident #1, 2026-06-02)
#
#   DO NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in this file or in any shell that runs anima.
#
# anima's Claude agents (Em's Opus/Sonnet escalation, Maya, Cy, Mo) bill the
# CLAUDE SUBSCRIPTION via claude-agent-sdk → the `claude` CLI's OAuth login.
# A present ANTHROPIC_API_KEY silently overrides that and bills the Anthropic
# API instead (in non-interactive mode the `claude` CLI ALWAYS uses the key
# when set — precedence ahead of subscription OAuth). That is what exhausted
# the API credits during the deferred Em live runs.
#
#   • Interactive subscription billing:  claude login   (verify: claude /status)
#   • Headless subscription billing:     claude setup-token  →  CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN
#     (and ANTHROPIC_API_KEY must be ABSENT — the key outranks the OAuth token)
#
# evals/vision_critic/score.py refuses to start if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set
# (override: --allow-api-key). See
# docs/anima-test-runs/2026-06-02-operational-incidents-remediation-plan.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Gemini — NB2 image gen + Gemini 3.1 Pro (Em via the `agy` CLI uses
# Google personal OAuth, not this key; this key is for the google-genai SDK path).
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# fal.ai — Seedance 2.0 motion generation.
FAL_KEY=

# Optional / situational (present in some pipeline + eval paths).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
SCRAPE_CREATORS_API_KEY=
BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY=
